<?xml version='1.0' encoding='ASCII'?>
<block>
  <name>ChirpSource</name>
  <key>ChirpSource</key>
  <category>hpsdr</category>
  <import>execfile("~/.grc_gnuradio/ChirpSource.py")</import>
  <make>ChirpSource($chirpRate, $sampRate, $direction, $amplitude)</make>
  <callback>set_chirpRate($chirpRate)</callback>
  <callback>set_sampleRate($sampRate)</callback>
  <callback>set_direction($direction)</callback>
  <callback>set_amplitude($amplitude)</callback>
  <param>
    <name>Chirp Rate</name>
    <key>chirpRate</key>
    <value>2000</value>
    <type>int</type>
  </param>
  <param>
    <name>Sample Rate</name>
    <key>sampRate</key>
    <value>48000</value>
    <type>int</type>
  </param>
  <param>
    <name>Direction</name>
    <key>direction</key>
    <value>0</value>
    <type>int</type>
  </param>
  <param>
    <name>Amplitude</name>
    <key>amplitude</key>
    <value>1</value>
    <type>float</type>
  </param>
  <source>
    <name>out</name>
    <type>complex</type>
    <vlen>1</vlen>
  </source>
<doc>
~/.grc_gnuradio/ChirpSource.py
Chirp goes from -samp_rate/2 to +samp_rate/2 (up).
or +samp_rate/2 to -samp_rate/2 (down).

Chirp Rate: KiloHertz per second
Sample Rate: Samples per second
Direction: 0 = down-chirp.  1= up-chirp
Amplitude: Maximum value of 1.0

</doc>
<grc_source></grc_source>
</block>
